{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-22","name":"Geoffrey de Worsley","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Geoffrey de Worsley","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Geoffrey"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Worsley"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Geoffrey Worsley","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1195–1268","fullLifespan":"1195–before 1268","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7799-128567-4218-88/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/182753933","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7799-128567-4218-88/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7799-128567-4218-88/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"(The) history of the Lancashire family of Pilkington and its branches from 1066 to 1600. Compiled from deeds, charters, wills, inquisitions ","description":"https://archive.org/details/thehistoryoflanc00pilk/page/n25/mode/2up","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-103817-2314-12/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/117354077","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-103817-2314-12/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7768-103817-2314-12/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1195","birthPlace":{"address":"Lancashire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.81849,"longitude":-2.62573,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"Liverpool, Lancashire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.41471,"longitude":-2.98096,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nPer British History Online: \n\"The lands which Richard de Worsley and Hugh the clerk had granted to Cockersand were by Abbot Roger given to Geoffrey son of Richard de Worsley at a rent of 2s., half a mark being payable at the death of himself, his wife, or heirs. In 1268 Richard de Worsley was in possession, so Geoffrey had died before this year.\n\n\"In 1254, he was one of the jury to inquire into certain trespasses on Thomas Grelley's parks. He occurs also in the Assize Roll of 1246. He made grants in Hulton.\n\n\"To his daughter Isabel, wife of Richard de Bolton, Geoffrey gave in free marriage certain land in Holeclough, with easements in Worsley, Mokenis excepted, the rent being a pair of white gloves; Ellesmere D. no. 115. This land Richard de Hulton in 1289 granted to his son Henry.\"\n\n«b»Children«/b»\nSons Richard and Roger; daughter Isabel.\n\n\"Geoffrey had two sons: ?Richard, who succeeded as heir, and Roger, who founded the line of the Worsleys of Kempnough, an old half-timbered house, still existing, about a mile distant from Wardley Hall, and which in the time of Elizabeth obtained an unenviable notoriety on account of the supposed demoniacal possession for a period of two years of some members of the family then inhabiting it.\"","sourceList":[{"title":"Geoffrey (Workesley) de Worsley (1195 - bef. 1268)","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Workesley-1","sourceUri":"QNDV-XH3"},{"title":"_Worsley Pages 376-392  A History of the County of Lancaster_ Volume 4. Originally published by Victoria County History, London, 1911_","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/lancs/vol4/pp376-392","sourceUri":"QNDV-87W"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"1","year":"1195","date":"1195","place":"Lancashire, England"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1217","date":"Abt 1217","place":"Lancashire, England","ag